    "summary": "I am an experienced researcher in Physics, nanodevices and Materials science having worked on 2D topological materials, transitional metal oxides and strongly correlated systems among others. I have studied a range of physical phenomena, including newly discovered Weyl fermions, electronic and thermo-electronic transport phenomena, FET characteristics, magnetization and magnetic domain behavior etc. I have worked in several high tech and multidisciplinary research institutes. I am skilled in thin film growth and characterization techniques, lithographically, e-beam lithography, single crystal growth,  Photo emission electron microscopy, transport and magnetic measurements among others.\nI have close to 30 research publications in peer reviewed journals. Details of these are available at\n\nhttps://scholar.google.com/citations?user=DQQC0PAAAAAJ&hl=en",
